INSERT INTO questions (test_set_id, question_number, question_text, option_a, option_b, option_c, option_d, correct_option, solution_text, sort_order) VALUES (19, 3, 'Leadership takes many forms, and not all great leaders are charismatic or loud. Quiet leaders often excel at listening, building consensus, and empowering others. They lead by example rather than command. In many organisations, the most effective teams are those where the leader creates an environment where every member feels heard and valued. This approach, sometimes called ''servant leadership,'' prioritises the growth and wellbeing of team members.
INSERT INTO questions (test_set_id, question_number, question_text, option_a, option_b, option_c, option_d, correct_option, solution_text, sort_order) VALUES (19, 4, 'Climate change refers to long-term shifts in global temperatures and weather patterns. While climate change has occurred naturally throughout Earth''s history, the current warming trend is occurring at an unprecedented rate. Scientists attribute this primarily to human activities, particularly the burning of fossil fuels, which releases greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide into the atmosphere. These gases trap heat in the atmosphere, creating a greenhouse effect. The consequences include rising sea levels, more frequent extreme weather events, and disruption to ecosystems worldwide.
INSERT INTO questions (test_set_id, question_number, question_text, option_a, option_b, option_c, option_d, correct_option, solution_text, sort_order) VALUES (19, 5, 'The concept of zero was independently developed by several ancient civilisations, including the Mayans and the Babylonians. However, the modern numerical system we use today, including the concept of zero as a number, originated in ancient India. Indian mathematicians developed a decimal place-value system that included zero as a placeholder and as a number in its own right. This system was later adopted and transmitted to Europe by Arab scholars, which is why our numerals are called ''Arabic numerals'' even though they originated in India.
INSERT INTO questions (test_set_id, question_number, question_text, option_a, option_b, option_c, option_d, correct_option, solution_text, sort_order) VALUES (19, 6, 'The Industrial Revolution, which began in Britain in the late 18th century, fundamentally transformed human society. Before this period, most people lived in rural areas and worked in agriculture. The invention of machines like the steam engine and the spinning jenny allowed goods to be produced in factories at unprecedented speeds. Cities grew rapidly as people moved from the countryside to work in these new factories. However, this rapid urbanisation led to overcrowding, poor sanitation, and harsh working conditions that took decades to address through labour laws and public health reforms.
